  "unit": {
    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Two structures. Present simple for the future (timetables/schedules: 'the train leaves at 6:30', 'the museum opens at 9'; contrast with will/going-to for plans & predictions) + want/tell/ask + person + to-infinitive (the required 'to', negative 'not to', object pronoun me/him/her/us/them, the 'want that' German-interference error). 30 vocab + 117 grammar (2 structures, floors 39+40 → 58+59), full v1 parity. 4 verify lenses clean after fixes. BIG fix: 50 grammar prompts were mislabeled lang:'en' while carrying German instructions, so the German got level-gated → 408 phantom V-5s; switched them to lang:'de' (matches every other unit; embedded English carriers are then checked by the level-gloss lens, not the gate). Relabeled 4 group-sorts off German category labels (Fahrplan/richtig/falsch/Objektform) → form exemplars ('leaves / opens' vs 'will / going to'), ✓/✗, 'to do'/'not to do'; the present-simple group-sorts were corrected twice (my first 'clock time' labels contradicted the members — both buckets had clock times — so the answers lens caught it; fixed to the real present-simple-vs-will/going-to axis). Reworded 'Objektform' out of an anagram prompt; rescrambled an 'ae'-digraph anagram ('esaelv'→'leevas'); raised 3 sentence-building chip budgets; granted the form exemplars (leaves/opens/will/going) + exams/win/late/phones. Translation lens 0 defects. 2 defensible enToDe warns (Aborigine→'Ureinwohner Australiens', ancestor→'Vorfahr/Ahne' — no umlaut trips the heuristic). Validate green."
